The paper deals with interference alignment (IA) in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines. However, based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication systems. The paper also mentions wireless wiretap networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the use of algebraic geometry in the theoretical framework could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
